\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {10}{\ignorespaces \textbf  {Modeling-ablation scope: parameter-space corruption can be generated back, dynamics-space corruption cannot.} \textbf  {A.} modWorm (Cook ODE, 7-D), \emph  {dynamics-space} corruption: injecting state noise collapses observable closeness to the clean simulator from $0.9999$ to $0.30$--$0.46$ (orange bars; grey are clean/intact). \textbf  {B.} FlyGym v2 (MuJoCo, 126-D), \emph  {dynamics-space} corruption: the integrator diverges on $4/6$ levels ($L_{\rm  final}{=}1.0$, orange), so there is no usable forward model for PGOB to act on. \textbf  {C.} BAAIWorm (NEURON 200-cell), \emph  {parameter-space} corruption: corrupted-start loss $L_0$ vs.\ after-PGOB loss $L_{\rm  final}$ per corruption level; $30/30$ cells improve ($L_{\rm  final}{<}L_0$), mean $\Delta L/L_0{=}-29.4\%$ over the full $L_0$--$L_5$ sweep (6 levels $\times $ 5 seeds). BAAIWorm corruption is applied in the 5-D scale-vector parameterisation, so the generation shows the scale axis absorbing weight noise rather than per-synapse repair.}}{25}{figure.10}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:hero6}{{10}{25}{\textbf {Modeling-ablation scope: parameter-space corruption can be generated back, dynamics-space corruption cannot.} \textbf {A.} modWorm (Cook ODE, 7-D), \emph {dynamics-space} corruption: injecting state noise collapses observable closeness to the clean simulator from $0.9999$ to $0.30$--$0.46$ (orange bars; grey are clean/intact). \textbf {B.} FlyGym v2 (MuJoCo, 126-D), \emph {dynamics-space} corruption: the integrator diverges on $4/6$ levels ($L_{\rm final}{=}1.0$, orange), so there is no usable forward model for PGOB to act on. \textbf {C.} BAAIWorm (NEURON 200-cell), \emph {parameter-space} corruption: corrupted-start loss $L_0$ vs.\ after-PGOB loss $L_{\rm final}$ per corruption level; $30/30$ cells improve ($L_{\rm final}{<}L_0$), mean $\Delta L/L_0{=}-29.4\%$ over the full $L_0$--$L_5$ sweep (6 levels $\times $ 5 seeds). BAAIWorm corruption is applied in the 5-D scale-vector parameterisation, so the generation shows the scale axis absorbing weight noise rather than per-synapse repair}{figure.10}{}}
